# IP Addressing & Subnetting

## IPv4 Structure
- 32 bits = 4 octets (each 0-255)
- Example: 192.168.1.1 = 11000000.10101000.00000001.00000001

---

## Public vs Private IP Ranges

| Type | Range | Use |
|------|-------|-----|
| Private | 10.0.0.0 - 10.255.255.255 | Large private networks |
| Private | 172.16.0.0 - 172.31.255.255 | Medium private networks |
| Private | 192.168.0.0 - 192.168.255.255 | Small private networks |
| Public | Everything else | Internet-facing |

---

## CIDR Notation

| CIDR | Network Bits | Host Bits | Total IPs | Usable IPs |
|------|--------------|-----------|-----------|------------|
| /8 | 8 | 24 | 16,777,216 | 16,777,214 |
| /16 | 16 | 16 | 65,536 | 65,534 |
| /24 | 24 | 8 | 256 | 254 |
| /30 | 30 | 2 | 4 | 2 |

### CIDR Examples
- 192.168.1.0/24: Network = 192.168.1.0, Hosts = 192.168.1.1 to 192.168.1.254
- 10.0.0.0/8: Network = 10.0.0.0, Hosts = 10.0.0.1 to 10.255.255.254
- 172.16.0.0/16: Network = 172.16.0.0, Hosts = 172.16.0.1 to 172.16.255.254

---

## Classful Addressing (Historical)

| Class | First Octet | Network Bits | Host Bits | Use |
|-------|-------------|--------------|-----------|-----|
| A | 1-126 | 8 | 24 | Large networks |
| B | 128-191 | 16 | 16 | Medium networks |
| C | 192-223 | 24 | 8 | Small networks |
| D | 224-239 | N/A | N/A | Multicast |
| E | 240-255 | N/A | N/A | Experimental |

### Special Addresses
- 0.0.0.0: Default route
- 127.0.0.0 - 127.255.255.255: Loopback (localhost is 127.0.0.1)
- 255.255.255.255: Limited broadcast

